|----|-------------|----------|------|---------------------|
| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |
